        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1977-03-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1977-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="188"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                <head>188. Letter From President <persName corresp="#p_CJEJ_1">Carter</persName> to
                    Former Chilean President <persName corresp="#p_FE_1">Frei</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d188fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                        Security Affairs, Staff Material, North/South, <persName corresp="#p_PCW_1"
                            >Pastor</persName>, Country Files, Box 9, Chile, 2-8/77. No
                        classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1977-03-02">March 2, 1977</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Mr. President:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I want to express to you my personal regret for any embarrassment that the press
                    reports, alleging that you have received payments from the Central Intelligence
                    Agency, may have caused you or the people of Chile.<note n="2" xml:id="d188fn2"
                        >David Binder, “More Heads of State Are Reported To Have Received C.I.A.
                        Payments,” <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi>, February 19, 1977, p. 9.
                        In a March 1 covering memorandum to <persName corresp="#p_CJEJ_1"
                            >Carter</persName>, attached but not printed, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BZ_1">Brzezinski</persName> noted that the letter to
                            <persName corresp="#p_FE_1">Frei</persName> “is deliberately a little
                        vaguer” than two other letters regarding similar allegations, because “there
                        was some cooperation with <persName corresp="#p_FE_1">Frei</persName> in the
                        past.” (Carter Library, National Security Affairs, Staff Material,
                        North/South, <persName corresp="#p_PCW_1">Pastor</persName>, Country Files,
                        Box 9, Chile, 2-8/77)</note> As you know, I have no control over the news
                    media in our country, and I cannot prevent groundless assertions. I do want you
                    to know, however, of my high personal esteem for you and for the people of
                    Chile, and I trust that these malicious stories will not cast a shadow over our
                    traditional friendship.</p>
                <p>With best wishes,</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJEJ_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Jimmy Carter</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
